{
  "texts": [
    "Zhang et al. (2022) conducted a meta-analysis of 23 empirical studies to review how teachers perceive STEM education and the effectiveness of various programs in enhancing these perceptions.",
    "Their study aimed to quantify the impact of different STEM interventions on teachers' understanding of STEM concepts, teaching methods, and student learning in STEM fields.",
    "According to Zhang et al. (2022), all interventions examined enhanced teachers' knowledge, teaching abilities, and perceptions of student learning in STEM.",
    "However, there is still a need to explore how these interventions can be tailored to different educational contexts within China, particularly in underrepresented regions.",
    "This tailoring is essential for ensuring that TPD programs meet the diverse needs of teachers across various contexts."
  ]
}